.TH "s5p_hash_prepare_request" 9 "s5p_hash_prepare_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
s5p_hash_prepare_request \- prepare request for processing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" s5p_hash_prepare_request
.BI "(struct ahash_request *req "  ","
.BI "bool update "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "req" 12
AHASH request
.IP "update" 12
true if UPDATE op
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note 1: we can have update flag _and_ final flag at the same time.
Note 2: we enter here when digcnt > BUFLEN (=HASH_BLOCK_SIZE) or
either req->nbytes or ctx->bufcnt + req->nbytes is > BUFLEN or
we have final op
